# Commit Scope Rule

## Scope boundary
- Commit only files inside this repository.
- Do not stage unrelated directories or global dotfiles.

## Must include for feature/release work
- Relevant source updates
- README updates when command/flow changes
- Rule updates when workflow policy changes

## Must exclude
- `~/.zshrc`
- unrelated `~/bin` files
- local caches, temporary artifacts, and secret files

## Pre-commit checklist
- `git status` shows only expected project files
- no secrets/path leaks detected
- verification commands executed for behavior-changing updates
